  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON:  Policy D1 of Islington's Unitary Development Plan 2002 sets out the requirement that the design and appearance of all new development should be of a high standard, appropriate to the overall streetscape, well planned to make the best use of the site & respect the scale, form and character of its surroundings.  The policy states that planning permission will be refused for schemes which are unsatisfactory in these respects. Policy D5 of Islington's Unitary Development Plan 2002 requires new buildings on cleared sites to respect the form, scale and grain of the surrounding townscape. The Local Planning Authority is neither satisfied that the design & appearance of the proposed scheme are adequate for a prominent gateway site which calls for a high quality, landmark development, nor that the proposed development takes appropriate account of its surroundings. The Authority considers the proposal to conflict with Policies D1 & D5 of the UDP."
